body.p:
If you use Zsh, add the following to your ~/.zshrc file. Zsh users can see the current directory if at a prompt, or any commands if a program is running.

if [ "$SHELL" = '/bin/zsh' ]
then
    case $TERM in
        rxvt|*term)
            precmd() { print -Pn "\e]0;%n@%m - %~\a" }
            preexec () { print -Pn "\e]0;%n@%m - $1\a" }
            ;;
    esac
fi
